Soak the rice in the water for at least 6 hours or overnight. Transfer the rice and the soaking liquid to the blender and whirl on its highest speed for a full 2 minutes. If youâ€™re using sweetener, blend it in with the rice. Strain through a fine-mesh strainer and discard the solids, Enjoy immediately, or serve cold or over ice. Kept refrigerated, rice milk will last for up to 1 week. Frozen rice milk will keep for up to 4 months. Variation: Horchata As anyone who lives within sniffing distance of a taqueria can tell you, horchata is an outrageously enjoyable beverage made from rice milk. On a hot day and/or with hot food, its sweet cinnamon coolness is most welcome. To make it, make the Rice Milk and soak I (3-inch) cinnamon stick in the water along with the rice. Include the cinnamon stick in the blender when pureeing the rice, along with a pinch of kosher salt and 4 tablespoons of your favorite sugar or natural sweetener, adding more to taste. Strain and enjoy immediately; or serve cold or over ice. Horchata will keep in the refrigerator for 3 days, but it does not freeze well.